After a video and discussion, they will be taking samples around the classroom and putting those samples on a petri dish to see if they can grow some germs.

post_text:
Castleford High School student Will Brackett has earned a position on the Idaho state National High School rodeo team and will be traveling with fellow teammates to Guthrie, Oklahoma, July 17-23, to compete at the 72nd annual National High School Finals Rodeo (NHSFR) in the boy’s cutting competition!

Featuring more than 1,650 contestants from 43 states, five Canadian Provinces, Australia, and Mexico, the NHSFR is the world’s largest rodeo. In addition to competing for more than than $150,000 in prizes, NHSFR contestants will also be competing for more than $375,000 in college scholarships and the chance to be named an NHSFR World Champion.

To follow your local favorites at the NHSFR, visit NHSRA.com. For ticket information, visit www.nhsfrlincoln.org.

Congratulations to Will Brackett!

Castleford School District and the Class of 2020 will be celebrating a formal graduation on June 27, 2020, at 8:00 p.m. on the football field. South Central District Health has approved our ceremony provided that the following social-distancing protocols are followed:

—Graduates, board members, and administration will be seated at least 6 feet apart.

—Attendees are urged to sit it family groups and keep spacing between family groups.

—Face masks are recommended, but not mandatory.

—Seating will be on a first-come, first-served basis. There will be some room on the bleachers on both sides of the field as well as room to sit on the football field. **Please plan to bring your own lawn chair.**

Congratulations to the graduating class of 2020!

post_text:
A message from Castleford School District food-service director Elaine Hape:

Wow, what a Ride!
It was a DELIGHT and a CHALLENGE to give a hand up to all the kids of our community by preparing breakfast and lunch meals each day. We love you and miss your smiling faces. It is said that it takes a village to raise a child. I know it takes a village to make and give out
3,000 meals a week. You are all truly loved! We have made and served 24,000 meals from March 30, 2020 to May 21, 2020.

THANK YOU to the bus drivers, the paraprofessionals, the teachers, administration, and our hard-working lunch staff!!! You guys are AWESOME! Our last day for lunch service was May 21, 2020. Thank you for being our students and children of our community. Time will tell, but we hope to see you in August.

Stay healthy, good job, and finish strong.

It was a DELIGHT and a CHALLENGE to give a hand up to all the kids of our community by preparing breakfast and lunch meals each day. We love you and miss your smiling faces. It is said that it takes a village to raise a child. I know it takes a village to make and give out
3,000 meals a week. You are all truly loved! We have made and served 24,000 meals from March 30, 2020 to May 21, 2020.

THANK YOU to the bus drivers, the paraprofessionals, the teachers, administration, and our hard-working lunch staff!!! You guys are AWESOME! Our last day for lunch service was May 21, 2020. Thank you for being our students and children of our community. Time will tell, but we hope to see you in August.

Stay healthy, good job, and finish strong.

post_text:
To Castleford Families,

The Idaho State Board of Education has mandated that schools do a “soft close” until April 20, 2020. This “soft close” means that there are to be no people in school buildings other than essential staff. Castleford School District's Food Service and Transportation Departments will be combining efforts during this time to provide food to our students. There will be two meals delivered via bus route for our students outside of the city limits, while students in town may come to the parking lot kitchen entrance to receive their food.

Busses will leave the school at 9:00 a.m. and should be at your stop sometime between 9:05 and 10:15 a.m. Please have someone at the stop to receive the food. In-town students may pick up their food at the school beginning at 9:15 a.m. These services will begin on Monday, March 30.

Sincerely,

Superintendent Lyle Bayley

post_text:
MEDIA RELEASE
IHSAA POSTPONES STATE CHAMPIONSHIPS
March 12, 2020 – (Boise, ID)
The Idaho High School Activities Association has postponed the remaining Winter State Championships. This includes (effective immediately) Debate and Cheer/Dance State Championships.
The IHSAA will continue to collaborate with Idaho’s public health authorities, including guidance from the Department of Health and Welfare, Center for Disease Control and the State Department of Education in order to help slow the transmission of the coronavirus.
We are working with GoFan, our on-line ticketing partners to ensure those who purchased State Cheer/Dance tickets will be reimbursed if necessary.
The IHSAA will continue to give updated information as this situation develops.
Please forward to your coaches, parents and fans.
https://castlefordschools.wordpress.com/2020/03/13/media-release/

post_text: Members of the Castleford FFA Chapter recently placed second in the South Magic Valley FFA Parliamentary Procedure Leadership Development Event. For this event, students had to take a written exam on parliamentary procedure and then demonstrate their knowledge in the form of a meeting in front of a panel of judges. Team members, left to right, were Justin Wells, Halle Derrick, Will Brackett, Rachel Evans, Katie Brackett, and Kila Matkovich. Will Brackett was the second high-score chairman within the district.

There will be an informational meeting for parents this evening at 6:00 p.m. regarding Waterford’s UPSTART Kindergarten School Readiness Program. The Waterford program can better prepare students for Kindergarten by providing them with a fun start in reading, math, or science in just fifteen to twenty minutes a day, five days per week.

This is only for Castleford's in-district children who will be four-years-old in September and who will be in the 2021-2022 Kindergarten class. Students will receive a computer as part of this free, at-home Kindergarten readiness program. For more information, please see the flyers below or call Mrs. Allred at 208-537-6511.

Members in attendance, left to right: (front row) Senator Bert Brackett, Ariah Olsen, Hailey Kaster, Josie Zimmers, Ashlynn Nicklas, Emily Pearson, Jamie Zimmers, Julia Lilly, and Trey Crabtree. (Back row) Oree Reynolds, Travis Wells, Tristin Loomis, Abby Olsen, Jordyn Kennison, and Hannah Gaalswyk.

post_text: The Castleford Agricultural Department would like to welcome Ms. Stouder to our program. During the next twelve weeks, she will be student-teaching to fulfill the final requirements for her Agricultural Education degree from the University of Idaho. During her tenure at Castleford, she will be teaching Greenhouse, Animal Science, Introduction to Mechanics, Introduction to Welding, Advanced Welding, and Agricultural Fabrications. Ms. Stouder is a 2015 graduate of Wendell High School, where she was actively involved in 4-H, FFA, softball, and basketball.
